Why senior developers are paid peanuts while executives are paid in millions?
text:
https://mobile.twitter.com/GergelyOrosz/status/1631326335783018497

Get in here. Y'all are paid peanuts while C level executive are paid in millions. Don't tell me some nonsensical reasons like high salaries, please adjust cost of living and you will get a bigger picture. Please read this:

https://mobile.twitter.com/oren_cass/status/1625491055201366023

https://www.cnet.com/personal-finance/cant-afford-the-basics-the-high-cost-of-living-is-about-way-more-than-inflation/

Plus homeless older developers and unemployed fresh graduates shows us a lousy picture. https://www.businessinsider.in/tech/a-55-year-old-developer-tells-us-what-its-like-to-face-homelessness-in-a-youth-obsessed-silicon-valley/articleshow/32879926.cms https://youtu.be/nT3VGI0V5Rs

My point is simple,senior developers who built the product should be paid more.

Let's discuss.

Tell HN: Cloudflare Pages serves wrong content
text:
Our website is hosted on Cloudflare pages. When we currently access it via our main domain, https://nxt.engineering, or via the Cloudflare Pages domain, https://nxt.pages.dev/, it serves the wrong content.

It works when I go to the specific hash: https://16f401e4.nxt.pages.dev/.

Of course, we're on the free plan and I can't even get in contact with Cloudflare (╯°□°）╯︵ ┻━┻.

Ask HN: Where can I get a list of NSFW domains to block
text: Hi all, I want to start a side project where I plan to build a cloud-hosted service that would allow a user to perform an action (e.g create a thumbnail) for an arbitrary domain a user inputs. I would like to restrict known NSFW sites so that I wouldn’t risk any reputation harm if someone attempts to use my service to visit sites with illegal (CSAM) or even NSFW content. What’s the best way to get a list of domains to prevent this?

Show HN: We Integrated ChatGPT API into our product in less than 24 hours
text:
Learning with a personal assistant is the future of education!
We have integrated ChatGPT API into our educational platform to help answer questions of students. The main aim of the assistant is to find mistakes and bugs in the codes of students and provide actionable feedback. It's like having a mentor right next to you.
Integrating this into our product took us less than 24 hours, and now we're the phase of collecting feedback and iterating.
Let me know what you think.
